text:
The Korean stall is good but a bit expensive. The bibimbap, kimchi soup, and soybean soup are all good. Healthy options too.
The soybean soup is a really good vegetarian option. And the portion is really big.
The ban mian is really good and cheap.
Thereâ€™s neverrrr seats at this canteen around dinner time

Don't order the salmon egg rice in Korean stall. I feel i hot cheated. With the price of 6.8, see the actual dish from my photo,  the salmon just a 4 very thin slice comparing the photo they showed which suppose to be salmon steak.

In my opinion, one of the top 3 best canteen in NTU. Ayam penyet is my favorite, especially the sambal (chilli). Must buy early cause sometimes it's sold out. Other stalls like Korean, Mala, Indian are famous too. I also recommend the milo or teh bing here!
Cosy and quiet place to have lunch or dinner with friends. Recommended is the nasi ayam penyet shop.

Came back to try the Korean food but realised the owner had changed. Now it serves measly portions. Food in picture cost $7.8? 30 cents for dabao. Wasn't as good as it used to be anymore... Didn't see an option to add cheese as well, which is really saddening :(
